## The Problem

When you define a component **inside another component's render**, React sees it as a new component type on every render, unmounts the old one, and mounts a fresh one — destroying focus.

```jsx
// ❌ BROKEN - InputComponent is redefined on every render
function Parent() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState('');

  // This creates a NEW component type every render
  const InputComponent = () => (
    <input
      value={value}
      onChange={e => setValue(e.target.value)}
    />
  );

  return <InputComponent />; // Unmounts/remounts every keystroke
}
```

---

## Why This Happens

```
Keystroke → setValue() → Parent re-renders
→ New InputComponent function created (different reference)
→ React sees different component type at same position
→ Unmount old tree, mount new tree
→ Focus lost
```

React uses **component identity** (the function/class reference) to decide whether to reuse or replace a subtree. A new reference = full replacement.

---

## Fix 1: Move the component outside (Best Solution)

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Defined once, stable reference
const InputComponent = ({ value, onChange }) => (
  <input value={value} onChange={onChange} />
);

function Parent() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState('');

  return (
    <InputComponent
      value={value}
      onChange={e => setValue(e.target.value)}
    />
  );
}
```

---

## Fix 2: Render JSX directly instead of a nested component

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT - No nested component at all
function Parent() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState('');

  return (
    <input
      value={value}
      onChange={e => setValue(e.target.value)}
    />
  );
}
```

---

## Fix 3: If you must define it inside, use `useCallback` + `useMemo`

```jsx
// ⚠️ Works but fragile — prefer Fix 1 or Fix 2
function Parent() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState('');

  // Stable component reference across renders
  // eslint-disable-next-line react/display-name
  const InputComponent = useMemo(
    () =>
      React.memo(({ value, onChange }) => (
        <input value={value} onChange={onChange} />
      )),
    [] // Empty deps = created once
  );

  return (
    <InputComponent
      value={value}
      onChange={e => setValue(e.target.value)}
    />
  );
}
```

> **Warning:** This is still risky. If `[]` deps ever need to change, you'll reintroduce the bug. Prefer Fix 1.

---

## Diagnosing This in Your Own Code

```jsx
// Add this to spot unstable component references
useEffect(() => {
  console.log('Component mounted'); // Fires every keystroke? You have this bug.
  return () => console.log('Component unmounted');
}, []);
```

```jsx
// React DevTools: enable "Highlight updates when components render"
// If you see a full blue flash (not green) on every keystroke → remounting
```

---

## Key Rules to Remember

| Pattern | Result |
|---|---|
| Component defined outside parent | ✅ Stable reference, no remount |
| Component defined inside render | ❌ New reference every render |
| Inline JSX (`<div>`) | ✅ Not a component, safe |
| `useMemo` component inside render | ⚠️ Works but avoid |
| `key` prop changed on same component |

# Debugging React Input Focus Loss

This happens because **React recreates the nested component on each render**, causing the input to unmount/remount (destroying focus).

## Root Causes

| Cause | Why It Breaks Focus |
|-------|---------------------|
| Creating component inline with unstable key | New reference = unmount old, mount new |
| Inline object/function as prop | Reference changes, triggers re-render |
| Missing `key` on list items | React can't track identity |
| Creating new components in render | Full subtree re-creation |

## Common Patterns That Cause This

### 1. Unstable Key (most common)

```jsx
// ❌ BROKEN - new key every render
function Parent() {
  return <Child key={Date.now()} />;
}

// ✅ FIXED - stable key
function Parent() {
  const id = useId(); // React 18+
  return <Child key={id} />;
}
```

### 2. Creating New Component References Inline

```jsx
// ❌ BROKEN - new component instance every render
function Parent() {
  return (
    <div>
      <div onClick={() => {}}><Input /></div>
      {/*    ^ new function reference */}
    </div>
  );
}

// ✅ FIXED - memoize or move outside
const FixedDiv = React.memo(({ children }) => <div>{children}</div>);

function Parent() {
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {}, []);
  return (
    <FixedDiv onClick={handleClick}>
      <Input />
    </FixedDiv>
  );
}
```

### 3. Inline Object Props

```jsx
// ❌ BROKEN - new object every render
function Parent() {
  return <Child style={{ color: 'red' }} />;
}

// ✅ FIXED - define outside or memoize
const RED_STYLE = { color: 'red' };
function Parent() {
  return <Child style={RED_STYLE} />;
}
```

### 4. Inline List Item Components

```jsx
// ❌ BROKEN - component recreated for each item
function List({ items }) {
  return items.map(item => (
    <ListItem key={item.id} item={item} />
  ));
}

// ✅ FIXED - define outside render
function List({ items }) {
  return items.map(item => (
    <ListItem key={item.id} item={item} />
  ));
}

const ListItem = React.memo(({ item }) => { /* ... */ });
```

